body:
This data set represents the most current depiction of the Appalachian National Scenic Trail centerline.

Locational information used to create this data set were obtained from Global Positioning Systems (GPS) survey data collected between 1999-2010 using mostly Trimble GPS equipment.
citation: Matthew C. Robinson(Originator), Appalachian Trail Conservancy(publisher), Appalachian Landscape Conservation Cooperative(administrator), 2011-02-11(Publication), Appalachian National Scenic Trail Centerline_applcc-shp-006, http://www.appalachiantrail.org/
purpose: This data set was developed to provide a depiction of the Appalachian National Scenic Trail in an usable and easily transferable format between parties so that it can correctly be represented on digital and printed maps; to assist staff members, agency partners, and trail-maintaining clubs with trail and land management duties; and to help local planning agencies, telecommunications companies, and other groups with planning activities, such as siting new developments that could have a substantial impact on the scenic quality of the Appalachian Trail.
rights: It is asked that proper citation (credit: Appalachian Trail Conservancy and National Park Service Appalachian Trail Park Office, 2010) be used on any materials (digital or printed) in which this information appears.; Although a large portion of this data is quite accurate, the information depicted in this data set is for general reference purposes only and does not represent legal survey information. The Appalachian Trail Conservancy, the National Park Service Appalachian Trail Park Office, agency partners (including other units of the National Park Service and the USDA Forest Service), and associated trail-maintaining clubs shall not be held responsible for use or misuse of this data.
